The paper proposes a novel RNN architecture for reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on understanding the underlying neural mechanisms for performance gain suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The use of the proposed architecture in a challenging continuous control task suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the emphasis on self-organization and compositionality suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
